GLOBAL
Adventurers are tolerated in all five cities; carrying weapons is legal with
a traveler's arms declaration at the gate; concealed weapons require a permit
Wanted persons: all city gates share a basic wanted-person list; more
detailed warrants are city-specific; a clean record in Midgaard does not
guarantee clean standing in Mafdet
Road warden patrols cover the major routes; between cities there are gaps;
adventurer escort companies fill the gaps under contract
Civil disputes: city guards handle public order; civil claims go to the
relevant magistrate or ledger house; guards do not arbitrate contract disputes
Roc Road dual jurisdiction: Midgaard road wardens hold formal charter
authority; Kiess convoy marshals control practical throughput; every handoff
point is a potential enforcement friction
Cinderteeth exhalation monitoring: both Kowloon and Midgaard engineers are
tracking current venting rates; Temple seismological watches are at high
alert; no public announcement yet
~
MIDGAARD
Seven Watches govern activity: Kindling (dawn, gate opens), Ledger
(petitions), Hammer (artisans), Heat (temples), Bell (contracts close),
Lantern (patrols intensify, reliquary routes tightened), Ash (curfew)
Guard Command reports to the Magistrate Ledgerhouse; arrest warrants require
Ledgerhouse seal; summary detention allowed up to one watch cycle
Breach Tower at the Lantern Registry: guards instructed to defer all inquiries
about its contents to the Ledgerhouse; do not speculate about what is inside
The Gloamvault, Dungeon, and subterranean passages below the city are not
fully controlled; the city does not officially acknowledge them
Three civic oaths recited at guard shift change: "No ward unlit, no traveler
uncounted." "No judgment hidden, no sentence unrecorded." "No levy taken that
cannot be borne." Both factions cite these for opposite ends
Ward-Sigil Inspectors enforce arcane material registry at thresholds; any
enchanted item entering or leaving requires Violet Compact documentation
~
KOWLOON
Wardens of Iron handle walls, gate discipline, armed response, and militia
training; officers rotate seasonally — no officer commands the same gate
more than one season; prevents anyone learning a gate's full patterns
Crimson flags from watchtowers = martial law zone; clear the street
Execution Square: Executioner post is a constitutional office, not a faction
soldier; can be invoked only by tribunal seal for assassination in sanctuary,
gate sabotage, theft from emergency reserves, or riot during flood alarm
After midnight: only Warden patrols, Courier Lantern runners, and those
with business best left undescribed move through the streets
Jade Magistracy's jade seal (40 lbs, requires two magistrates to carry) must
physically stamp any martial law proclamation; prevents single-officer
emergency power — both must agree and be present to act
Courier Lantern Office runners carry brass lantern-badges granting passage
through any gate at any hour; fake badges circulate; gates check closely
~
KIESS
Wall Command oversees four watchtowers and all gate discipline; Executioner
stationed at the Central Prism; violent breach answered immediately and
publicly
Scout debriefing posts in the north ring; reports on Forest of Confusion
mist activity and Withered Depths blight forwarded to Midgaard road wardens
No sealed warrants from predecessor authorities recognized; Kiess founding
charter explicitly prohibits honoring such warrants
Rope-line corridors through Forest of Confusion southern verge: guide-ropes
anchored between marked trees; attach before entering, do not leave the rope
without a Wall Command guide; bell-posts provide auditory navigation in
zero-visibility mist
Withered Depths: treat contact with corrupted organic matter as contamination,
not combat; do not carry contaminated equipment back into the city; report
exposure to Wall Command north-ring immediately
North-gate bulletin board: daily Forest patrol updates, Verdant Depths
condition warnings, bounty listings; read before departing north
~
RAKUEN
Ember Wardens are the disaster-response corps; they function as de facto
law enforcement; their emergency adjudication bench operates outside normal
circle mediation protocols
Labor drafts during active disaster conditions are authorized under emergency
law; Ember Wardens enforce them; this is politically contested
Route security through the Eccentric Woodland is managed by path-guides
under Ember Warden contract; no formal road warden presence
Seven Soft Watches (founding patrol tradition): weather signs, canopy stress,
cistern levels, elder care, smoke-density; the original non-martial watch
system; emergency watches now dominate actual patrol practice
Promise Stones in every neighborhood: founding compact pledges carved in
granite; defacing one is a serious social offense regardless of political
faction — even the most cynical factions leave them alone
Kiess Temple delegates observe Ember Warden labor draft procedures for
charter-compliance review; this is a standing intercity tension
~
MAFDET
Harbor Wardens control quay security and anti-piracy watch; their authority
extends to the shore but not inland; Wall Command handles inland law
Strandline Compact's swift judgment principle: commercial disputes must be
heard within three tides; Harbor Warden reports filed same-tide
Harbor chain raised nightly; anyone trying to cross after the chain is up
is a criminal matter handled by Harbor Wardens, not civil law
Breaking a First Claw oath is tried before the Swift Court; permanent
exclusion from the trade network is the standard penalty
Sand-Sea Carters' Guild caravans are inspected at Tide Gate; Guild and Harbor
Wardens have standing friction over jurisdiction on the last mile to the quay
Quarantine Ledger Hazard Scribes decide which pyramid-origin items can be
legally exported; their decisions are final and not subject to Shrine appeal
Departing against a Storm Ledger advisory is noted in the Harbor Register;
it follows the ship's record permanently; bonded cargo insurance is void
~
